records.addlTxt: No contact with Officer Noah DiPuma unless in an official capacity and no contact with Kwik Trip stores in Douglas County

3:32 PM Defendant Colton Travis O'Neill appeared by video, in custody.  Prosecuting attorney Allison E. Cogbill in court for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney Van Ert appeared by video, in court for defendant Colton Travis O'Neill. Defendant updated address. Attorney Van Ert received complaint, waives reading and requests preliminary hearing. State requests $1,000 cash bail with conditions of no contact with Officer Noah DiPuma unless in an official capacity and no contact with Kwik Trip stores. Defendant has two fta's in 2020 and 2021. Defendant has very lengthy criminal history. Attorney Van Ert states defendant has lived locally for several years. Attorney Van Ert asks for a signature bond or $250 cash bail. Court orders $1,000 cash bail with conditions of no contact with Officer Noah DiPuma unless in an official capacity and no contact with Kwik Trip stores in Douglas County.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 21, 2022 at 09:45 am.
